title: Hate on bro split via /r/Fitness
body:
Whats up with all the hate on your average bro split Chest-triceps Back-biceps Shoulders-forearm Legs

Bench focus on chest, deadlift on back, ohp on shoulders and squats on legs.

I’ve seen people trashing it saying that it’s inefficient but have yet to get it explained. You think it lacks leg work? Add squats to your back day

summary: Workout Routine When Sick, When I Just Don't Want To
title: Workout Routine When Sick, When I Just Don't Want To
body:
workout routine when sick



Now, I need to admit I am not terribly sick. Just some sinus pain that is going into my teeth. What makes it worse is the pain going into my teeth. I do not do well with tooth pain. So, now I am facing doing my workout routine when sick.



When I hurt I just like to curl up and do nothing. I do not do sick well. Even when I was a child I hated pain. So far in my journey to get healthy I lost 11 pounds. I need to keep this up. I cannot let myself slip into being unhealthy. So, when I am not feeling well I am gentler with my self and I draw strength from the Lord. He is the only one who can get me past my depression that comes with being physically in pain.



I need to guard my health as if my life depended on it as author Alexander Hellene writes about in his article Sick but Not Dead. Really enjoy when you are feeling good, push to make healthy choices. For when you are not feeling well those choices are harder to make.



Outside sources



How to Stay Healthy When Your Family Is Sick





How to Avoid Getting Sick, Stay Healthy & Be Well

summary: Fortunately, protein is not an especially hard macronutrient to get enough of, whatever your requirements, and in the UK we...
caption:
Fortunately, protein is not an especially hard macronutrient to get enough of, whatever your requirements, and in the UK we generally eat way more of it than we actually need to. According to the National Diet And Nutrition Survey, adults in the UK consume about 45-55% more protein than required each day. The reason for that isn’t that everyone in the country is seeking to bulk up – it’s that protein is found in significant amounts in a wide variety of delicious foods that we’re already eating regularly.

summary: Vegan Cinnamon Streusel Pancakes
title: Vegan Cinnamon Streusel Pancakes
body:
https://www.veganricha.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Vegan-Coffee-Cake-Cinnamon-Streusel-Pancakes-veganricha-6970-001.jpg

These Vegan Cinnamon Streusel Pancakes are a perfect treat for Valentines or a special day. A delicious fluffy vanilla pancake topped with a cinnamon streusel for a coffee cake pancake. Make the pancakes in cookie cutters to make a pancake tower! Vegan Soyfree Nutfree Recipe. Glutenfree Option  Jump to Recipe  

We all love a decadent breakfast once in a while and these Cinnamon Streusel Pancakes are just perfect for that! These tall soft pancakes are a cinnamon streusel cake/coffee cake in pancake form! If you make them using cookie cutters, then they are almost a Cinnamon streusel cake, no baking needed! 

The batter is a simple vanilla cake batter that is cooked in a skillet. Sprinkle some streusel on one side, flip, cook and serve. I use Cookies cutters to make cake tower like my popular Chocolate Cake for 2, Chocolate Pancake tower (so decadent and ready in 20 mins!). You can make regular pancakes with the batter as well. Drizzle with maple, icing or top with some cream cheese frosting or whipped coconut cream and fruits!

Continue reading: Vegan Cinnamon Streusel Pancakes
